<paragraph blockId="8.[189,303,499,525]" box="[189,303,499,525]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,499,525]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,499,525]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1400,545,1065]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The taxonomic history of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[501,742,545,571]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Hediste" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[501,742,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hediste diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather complex and has not been fully resolved. The original description was “body subdepressed, parapodia tapered with chaetae” (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller O. F." box="[1125,1337,580,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44398" refString="Muller O. F. 1776. Zoologiae Danicae Prodromus, seu Animalium Daniae et Norvegiae Indigenarum Characters, Nomina, et Synonyma Imprimis Popularium. Hallageriis, Havniae [Copenhagen]. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13268" type="book" year="1776">Müller 1776: 217</bibRefCitation>
), and no Greenlandic name or 
<typeStatus box="[495,546,616,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
locality was indicated; after invoking the ICZN, the Commission has moved to conclude that “the 
<typeStatus box="[545,596,652,678]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
locality has not been clarified” (
<bibRefCitation author="Oug E. &amp; Bakken T. &amp; Kongsrud J. A." box="[999,1262,651,678]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="217 - 236" refId="ref44615" refString="Oug E., Bakken T. &amp; Kongsrud J. A. 2014. Original specimens and type localities of early described polychaete species (Annelida) from Norway, with particular attention to species described by O. F. Muller and M. Sars. Memoirs of Museum Victoria 71: 217 - 236. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2014.71.17" type="journal article" year="2014">
Oug 
<emphasis box="[1062,1117,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2014: 220
</bibRefCitation>
). However, recommendation 76A1.3 is to take into account “the original description of the taxon”. The second line for the original description includes two references: “Würm. 104, t. 6, Str. S. 1, p. 198, 2?” The first is a previous paper by the author (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller O. F." box="[595,747,757,783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44346" refString="Muller O. F. 1771. Von Wurmern des sussen und salzigen Wassers. Seinect und Faber, Copenhagen. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 50349  page / 5 / mode / 1 up [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="url" year="1771">Müller 1771</bibRefCitation>
), whereas the latter is a paper: “Physik og oeconomisk Beskrievelse over fogderiet Söndmör” by Hans Ström (published in Soröe [Sorø, 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1277,791,818]" name="Denmark" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Denmark</collectingCountry>
] in 1762). We could not find the latter, but we found two editions of the former which contain an extended description (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller O. F." box="[337,608,862,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44346" refString="Muller O. F. 1771. Von Wurmern des sussen und salzigen Wassers. Seinect und Faber, Copenhagen. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 50349  page / 5 / mode / 1 up [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="url" year="1771">Müller 1771: 102–111</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 6 figs 1–6) and indications that the specimens were collected in Copenhagen. This information complies with the recommendation, and consequently the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,898,924]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
locality should be Copenhagen, 
<collectingCountry box="[575,688,933,959]" name="Denmark" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Denmark</collectingCountry>
. It was reiterated in the second edition (Müller 1880: 110). Furthermore, specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[634,813,968,994]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Hediste" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[634,813,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Baltic Sea include at least two different species, and this has complicated solving what we should regard as this biological species (
<bibRefCitation author="Virgilio M. &amp; Fauvelot C. &amp; Constantini F. &amp; Abbiati M. &amp; Backeljau T." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1980 - 1994" refId="ref46360" refString="Virgilio M., Fauvelot C., Constantini F., Abbiati M. &amp; Backeljau T. 2009. Phylogeography of the common ragworm Hediste diversicolor (Polychaeta: Nereididae) reveals cryptic diversity and multiple colonization events across its distribution. Molecular Ecology 18: 1980 - 1994. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 294 X. 2009.04170. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Virgilio 
<emphasis box="[189,240,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tosuji H. &amp; Bastrop R. &amp; Gotting M. &amp; Park T. &amp; Hong J. - S. &amp; Sato M." box="[329,539,1038,1065]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1385 - 1402" refId="ref45940" refString="Tosuji H., Bastrop R., Gotting M., Park T., Hong J. - S., Sato M. 2019. Worldwide molecular phylogeny of common estuarine polychaetes of the genus Hediste (Annelida: Nereididae), with special referenc to interspecific common haplotypes found in southern Japan. Marine Biodiversity 49: 1385 - 1402. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 018 - 0917 - 2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Tosuji 
<emphasis box="[408,460,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1400,1096,1404]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<bibRefCitation author="Orsted A. S." box="[189,396,1096,1125]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44560" refString="Orsted A. S. 1843. Annulatorum Danicorum Conspectus, Fasc. 1. Maricolae. Wahlianae, Hafniae [Copenhagen]. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 44441  page / 3 / mode / 1 up [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="url" year="1843">Örsted (1843: 23)</bibRefCitation>
provided a description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1776" box="[701,925,1096,1122]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[701,925,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Nereis diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and included illustrations of the anterior end, one jaw and one parapodium (pl. 4 figs 66, 68, 73). From the description, he emphasized that the tentacular cirri could reach segments 5–6, that dorsal cirri were short, parapodial ligules tapered and the notopodia had three ligules. He also indicated that this was a very common species living in sediments along Danish coasts, and in the synonymy he listed the species that 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathke H." box="[1161,1347,1237,1263]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="290 - 454" refId="ref44938" refString="Rathke H. 1837 a. Zur Fauna der Krym. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. Petersbourg (Memoirs des Savants etrangers) 3: 290 - 454. Available from http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / bibliography / 11609  / summary [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1837">Rathke (1837a)</bibRefCitation>
had recorded as 
<taxonomicName authority="? Orsted" authorityName="Orsted" box="[332,648,1272,1301]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Lycoris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulsatoria">
<emphasis box="[332,563,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lycoris pulsatoria?</emphasis>
Örsted
</taxonomicName>
relied on the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathke H." box="[1085,1267,1272,1298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="290 - 454" refId="ref44938" refString="Rathke H. 1837 a. Zur Fauna der Krym. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. Petersbourg (Memoirs des Savants etrangers) 3: 290 - 454. Available from http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / bibliography / 11609  / summary [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1837">Rathke (1837a)</bibRefCitation>
and on the additional detailed account of its anatomy published separately (
<bibRefCitation author="Rathke H." box="[968,1142,1307,1334]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44996" refString="Rathke H. 1837 b. De Bopyro et Nereide: Commentationes Anatomico-Physiologicae Duae. Frantzen, Rigae and Dorpati [Riga and Tartu, Estonia]. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14421" type="book" year="1837">Rathke 1837b</bibRefCitation>
). Because the typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1776" box="[189,365,1342,1368]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[189,365,1342,1368]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">N. diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the recorded specimens of 
<emphasis box="[734,901,1342,1368]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName box="[734,889,1342,1368]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Lycoris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulsatoria">L. pulsatoria</taxonomicName>
?
</emphasis>
have three notopodial ligules, he regarded them as synonymous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[187,1400,1435,1673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation author="Malmgren A. J." box="[413,708,1435,1462]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref44120" refString="Malmgren A. J. 1867. Annulata Polychaeta Spetsbergiae, Groenlandiae, Islandiae et Scandinaviae hactenus cognita. Frenckelliana, Helsingsforsiae [Helsinki]. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13358" type="book" year="1867">Malmgren (1867: 48–49)</bibRefCitation>
used the number of notopodial ligules in his key to genera, and for species having three ligules he proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1867" box="[778,866,1471,1497]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Hediste" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[778,866,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hediste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1776" box="[945,1123,1471,1497]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[945,1123,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">N. diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its only species and listing 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathke, 1843" authorityName="Rathke" authorityYear="1843" box="[270,529,1506,1532]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sarsi">
<emphasis box="[270,362,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">N. sarsi</emphasis>
Rathke, 1843
</taxonomicName>
, described from Molde, 
<collectingCountry box="[818,914,1506,1532]" name="Norway" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Norway</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Frey &amp; Leuckart, 1847" authorityName="Frey &amp; Leuckart" authorityYear="1847" box="[976,1393,1506,1532]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="depressa">
<emphasis box="[976,1114,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">N. depressa</emphasis>
Frey &amp; Leuckart, 1847
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[370,495,1541,1567]" name="Germany" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Helgoland</collectingCountry>
, as synonyms. Malmgren did not use the diagnostic anchylosed neurofalcigers in his diagnosis, nor in the species description, and did not illustrate them. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ehlers E." box="[1093,1317,1576,1603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="269 - 748" refId="ref41422" refString="Ehlers E. 1868. Die Borstenwurmer (Annelida Chaetopoda) nach systematischen und anatomischen Untersuchungen dargestellt 2: 269 - 748. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 1985162  page / 321 / mode / 1 up [accessed 16 Sep. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1868">Ehlers (1868: 554)</bibRefCitation>
added 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnston, 1840" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1840" box="[191,554,1611,1638]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevimanus">
<emphasis box="[191,364,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">N. brevimanus</emphasis>
Johnston, 1840
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[758,844,1611,1637]" name="Ireland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ireland</collectingCountry>
, to the list of synonyms, provided a complete description and indicated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[542,781,1647,1673]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Hediste" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diversicolor">
<emphasis box="[542,781,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hediste diversicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could also be found in fresh-water environments.
</paragraph>
